detail_description: Armazém do Sal is a charming restaurant located in the heart of Funchal, Portugal, housed within a former salt warehouse. The restaurant boasts an inviting ambiance with wooden beams and stone walls. It offers a small but dedicated vegan menu featuring three main dishes including soya moussaka with roasted aubergine, lentil salad with roasted vegetables, and barley salad with caramelized baby vegetables.
name: Armazém do Sal - Michelin Guide 2024
address: R. da Alfândega 135, São Martinho, 9000-059 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Vila do Peixe is a seafood restaurant located in the lively Camara de Lobos, just a short drive from Funchal. The restaurant offers a live fish counter where diners can select their own fresh seafood, including tuna, sea bream, and black scabbard fish. These are simply grilled with salt and served alongside stunning views of the city and bay through floor-to-ceiling windows.
name: Restaurante Vila do Peixe
address: R. Dr. João Abel de Freitas 30A, 9300-048 Câmara de Lobos, Portugal

detail_description: Il Gallo D'Oro is a renowned fine dining restaurant located in The Cliff Bay hotel in Funchal, Madeira. This upscale establishment has been awarded two Michelin stars and is celebrated as the best restaurant on the island and even throughout Portugal at times. Specializing in Iberian Cuisine, Il Gallo D'Oro prides itself on using locally sourced produce to ensure the freshness and quality of its dishes.
name: Il Gallo D'Oro
address: The Cliff Bay hotel, Estrada Monumental 147, São Martinho, 9004-532 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Desarma is a contemporary restaurant that focuses on the simplicity and flavor of food. The chef's expertise shines through in every dish, creating a unique dining experience. The restaurant offers both 6 and 9 course menus, featuring a blend of local cuisine with innovative twists. Guests are impressed by the impressive open kitchen and stunning views over Funchal bay. The attentive and professional staff adds to the overall exceptional dining experience at Restaurante Desarma.
name: Restaurante Desarma
address: The Views Baía, R. das Maravilhas 74, 9000-177 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Design Centre Nini Andrade Silva is a must-visit attraction for those seeking a unique and immersive experience. The center features stunning gardens that seamlessly blend with nature, providing visitors with an unforgettable environment. It also houses an innovative museum designed by renowned architect Paulo David, showcasing gravity-defying contemporary architecture that contrasts beautifully with the traditional island surroundings. Inside, visitors can explore exhibition spaces, workshops, and a museum for study purposes.
name: Design Centre Nini Andrade Silva
address: Estrada da Pontinha, Forte de Nossa Senhora da Conceição, 9000-726 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Lá ao Fundo is a must-visit in Funchal's Old Town, offering a unique gastronomic experience with its fusion of Mediterranean, European, Portuguese, and modern cuisine. The restaurant boasts a welcoming and laid-back ambiance that makes diners feel at home.
name: Restaurante Lá ao Fundo
address: R. Portão de São Tiago 17A, 9060-250 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Avista Restaurant, located within Les Suites at Cliff Bay, offers a unique dining experience with its Mediterranean and Asian cuisine overseen by chef Benoit Sinthon. The restaurant's century-old house setting provides a charming backdrop for enjoying the diverse menu options, including a la carte dishes designed for sharing and bistro-style tasting menus. With its Michelin-starred quality and stunning views of the Atlantic Ocean, Avista is celebrated as one of Funchal's top dining destinations.
name: Avista Restaurant
address: Estrada Monumental 145, São Martinho, 9004-532 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in the enchanting heart of Funchal's old town, William Restaurant is a true gem that embodies elegance and sophistication. Set within a beautifully restored 18th-century mansion, this Michelin-starred dining destination invites guests on an exquisite culinary adventure that celebrates the rich flavors of Madeira. With stunning views overlooking Porto de Funchal, diners can savor innovative dishes crafted from the finest local ingredients while enjoying a contemporary twist on traditional European cuisine.
name: William Restaurant
address: Estrada Monumental 139, São Martinho, 9000-098 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Museu Café & Petisco is a charming cafe and bar located near the Museu de Arte Sacra in Funchal. The chef draws inspiration from Portuguese and Madeiran ingredients as well as international flavors, resulting in delicious and lovingly prepared food. The lunch menu changes daily, offering a variety of options at great value. With outdoor seating facing the main square, it's an ideal spot to enjoy coffee, cocktails, or a satisfying meal.
name: Museu Café & Petisco
address: Praca do Município 85, São Martinho, 9000-043 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: In Funchal, the Allegro Madeira Adults Only hotel offers great value for money with its stunning panoramic views of the Atlantic Ocean. The hotel's 124 bright rooms are decorated in blue tones and it is conveniently located close to the historic center and the area of Lido. Guests can enjoy traditional and international cuisine at the hotel's restaurant, as well as delicious cocktails at the Rooftop Bar 360 while taking in the horizon view.
name: Restaurante Atlantic
address: Estrada Monumental 179, São Martinho, 9000-100 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Barreirinha Bar Café is a popular spot in Funchal, located just 4km outside of the town center. It offers a versatile experience, serving as a cafe during the day and transforming into a lively bar at night. The menu features easy-to-eat items such as burgers, sandwiches, burritos, and salads. The location on a hillside provides stunning views of the ocean from small outside tables on the terrace.
name: Barreirinha Bar Café
address: Largo do Socorro 1, 9060-305 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Casal da Penha is a charming, family-owned restaurant located in the heart of Funchal. The traditional Madeiran and Portuguese dishes served here include bolo do caco, black scabbard fish with bananas, Madeiran-style tuna, espetada, and passionfruit pudding with Madeira wines. The restaurant also offers a daily variety of fresh fish and seafood purchased at the local market.
name: Restaurante Casal da Penha
address: Beco da Ataíde 1, São Martinho, 9000-604 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante O Portão is a charming culinary gem nestled in the heart of Funchal's Old Town, offering a delightful blend of seafood dishes and Mediterranean, European, and Portuguese cuisine. The restaurant prides itself on serving traditional Madeiran fare, with a focus on fresh, seasonal fish sourced from the catch of the day.
name: Restaurante O Portão
address: R. Portão de São Tiago, 9060-250 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Funchal's Old Town, Restaurante Taberna Ruel is a charming eatery that stands out with its eye-catching yellow facade on Rua de Santa Maria. This beloved spot offers a delightful blend of Madeiran cuisine and traditional European dishes, all complemented by an impressive selection of Portuguese wines. Guests can choose to dine al fresco on the lively pedestrian street, enjoy a cozy meal under the historic stone arches indoors, or savor grilled steaks in the serene rear courtyard.
name: Restaurante Taberna Ruel
address: Rua de Santa Maria 119, 9060-291 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Located in Funchal, Madeira Island, Loja do Chá is a beloved destination for tea lovers. Since 2003, this charming teahouse and café has been offering an extensive selection of around 200 different teas and infusions known for their exceptional quality and unique character. Whether you're a tea enthusiast or just looking to explore new flavors, the diverse range of international teas available here is sure to captivate your senses.
name: Loja do Chá
address: R. do Sabão 33 35, São Martinho, 9000-056 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Located in Funchal, Portugal, Akua is a renowned dining spot celebrated for its exceptional seafood. Chef Julio Pereira showcases his innovative take on Portuguese flavors with dishes like fried codfish tacos, white fish ceviche, and mussels in Jaipur sauce. The restaurant has garnered praise and was honored with a Tripadvisor Travellers Choice award. Additionally, it is featured on the menus of popular local establishments such as Gaviao Novo and La ao Fundo.
name: Akua
address: R. Dos Murcas 6, São Martinho, 9000-058 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Ristorante Villa Cipriani in Funchal is a traditional Italian restaurant with a romantic ambiance and stunning sea views, making it perfect for special occasions. The alfresco terrace offers an idyllic setting to enjoy dishes like rosemary focaccia, carpaccio, eggplant parmigiana, tuna with sesame crust, and mixed grilled fish and seafood. Don't miss the opportunity to indulge in their delicious cre brulee.
name: Ristorante Villa Cipriani
address: Estrada Monumental 143, São Martinho, 9000-098 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante do Forte is a dining establishment located within the historic Sao Tiago Fortress, offering a unique and memorable experience. The restaurant boasts a diverse menu featuring both local and international dishes, with spectacular views of the harbor adding to the ambiance. The setting within the 17th-century fortress creates an elegant atmosphere, making it an ideal choice for a special evening out.
name: Restaurante do Forte
address: Tv. do Forte 3, 9060-123 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: O Celeiro, located in downtown Funchal, is a well-established restaurant known for its warm hospitality and traditional Portuguese cuisine. The interior is adorned with antique woods, regional tapestries, and traditional tile works, creating a cozy atmosphere. The menu offers a variety of authentic Madeiran and Portuguese dishes, including specialties like bacalhau and grilled meats. With personalized service and generous portions at reasonable prices, this restaurant provides an excellent dining experience.
name: O Celeiro
address: R. dos Aranhas 22, São Martinho, 9000-044 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Casa Madeirense is a charming restaurant located in the hotel zone near Cliff Bay Resort, housed in a restored building adorned with intricate tile work and hand-painted murals. The menu features an abundance of fresh seafood, including lobster, as well as regional specialties like espada prepared in various ways and the house specialty tornedo. In addition to traditional Madeiran dishes, they also offer pizzas for those seeking something different.
name: Casa Madeirense
address: Estrada Monumental 153, São Martinho, 9000-098 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The Golden Gate Grand Cafe is a classic and elegant dining spot located in the heart of Funchal, offering a glimpse into the traditional Madeira atmosphere. Situated at the lower level of Hotel Quinta da Casa Branca, this luxurious Manor House features a distinctive dining room with an al fresco terrace. Established since 1814, it provides a charming ambiance for patrons to enjoy Portuguese dishes or British-style afternoon tea.
name: Golden Gate Grand Cafe
address: Av. Arriaga N° 29, São Martinho, 9000-060 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The cafe Cabo Aéreo Café is a great place to get your food and drinks. They have grill options, but the real draw is the wide variety of Mediterranean and European dishes. There's also a bar where you can order cocktails or beers. The seating is outdoors so you can enjoy the weather while you eat, and they have wheelchair accessible access. Plus, they offer free wifi.
name: Cabo Aéreo Café Restaurant
address: São Jorge, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled on the 16th floor of the Savoy Palace, Galáxia Skyfood offers a dining experience that feels like an enchanting journey among the stars. The restaurant's cozy ambiance features beautifully painted ceilings, setting the stage for Chef Carlos Goncalves' innovative five- to seven-course tasting menus.
name: Galáxia Skyfood | Skybar
address: Av. do Infante 25, São Martinho, 9004-542 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Tokos is a regional restaurant in Madeira known for its warm and friendly owners who personally attend to both the dining room and kitchen. The chef takes pride in offering a variety of freshly cooked dishes, with a particular emphasis on fresh fish. Guests can expect a personalized experience as the chef often visits tables to discuss the menu and daily seafood offerings. The restaurant's dedication to quality is evident in its carefully prepared meals, which may take some time due to individual cooking.
name: Restaurante Tokos
address: Estrada Monumental 169, São Martinho, Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Bar Number Two is a local favorite for those looking to socialize and enjoy a good drink. The bar has a wide range of reasonably priced drinks, as well as homemade ponchas with fresh, real juice.
name: Bar Number Two
address: R. Dom Carlos I 54 56, 9060-051 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled on the southern coast of Madeira, Doca do Cavacas is a hidden gem that perfectly blends relaxation and stunning natural beauty. This charming beach, also known as Poca do Gomes, lies conveniently between the Lido and Formosa beach in Funchal. With its inviting volcanic swimming pool and direct sea access, it offers breathtaking views of the Atlantic Ocean and Cabo Girao skywalk—the highest cliff in Europe.
name: Doca do Cavacas
address: Rua da Ponta da Cruz 66, 9000-250 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Pátio das Babosas is a great Portuguese restaurant in the town of Funchal, Madeira. The food is delicious and the portions are large, making it perfect for a quick bite or a full meal. It can be quite busy so be prepared to wait awhile, but the views from the outdoor seating are worth the wait. The bar serves alcohol, and there is free wifi available.
name: Pátio das Babosas
address: Largo das Babosas 16, Monte, Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Combatentes is a no-nonsense, family-run restaurant that serves scabbardfish, espetada (barbecued beef on a skewer), lots of seafood and a couple of tasty vegetarian dishes. It has a simple dining room and is good for Portuguese wine lovers.
name: Restaurante dos Combatentes
address: R. de São Francisco, São Martinho, 9000-050 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Local Shop is a charming bar and cafe located in Monte, offering a selection of local craft beers and delicious coffee. Despite its proximity to the Monte cable car, it manages to maintain an authentic atmosphere without being overly touristy. The outdoor seating area provides stunning views of the valley, making it an ideal spot to relax and enjoy a drink or snack. Visitors praise the friendly staff and recommend stopping by for a coffee and homemade cake deal.
name: LocalShop
address: Quiosque do Teleférico do Jardim Botânico / Babosas, Largo das Babosas, Monte, 9050-542 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: As Vides Restaurant, located in Camara dos Lobos, Madeira, has been a culinary staple since 1950. The restaurant is known for its traditional and welcoming atmosphere, serving up authentic regional dishes with a focus on locally-sourced ingredients. One of the highlights is the espetada (kebab), where the seasoning is hand-crushed and rubbed onto each piece of meat before being skewered and cooked on an acacia wood grill.
name: As Vides Restaurant
address: R. da Achada 17, 9325-017 Ilha Da Madeira, Portugal

detail_description: The Wanderer is a unique restaurant in Funchal that draws inspiration from the extensive travels of its owner, who has explored more than 100 countries. The diverse menu showcases culinary delights from various parts of the world, encompassing dishes like Indian curry, Thai pad thai, and Lebanese falafel. Offering a vibrant array of flavors and aromas, this establishment prides itself on sourcing fresh and top-notch ingredients locally.
name: The Wanderer
address: Centro Comercial Olimpo, Av. do Infante, São Martinho, 9000-015 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in a picturesque location with stunning ocean views, Cris's Place is a highly recommended restaurant in Madeira known for its gourmet European cuisine. The well-curated menu features locally sourced ingredients and is updated twice a year, offering Instagram-worthy dishes that are as visually appealing as they are delicious. The restaurant boasts a lovely terrace and floor-to-ceiling windows, allowing guests to enjoy the scenic surroundings both indoors and outdoors.
name: Cris's Place
address: R. da Casa Branca 34A, São Martinho, 9000-088 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Cantinho da Serra is a charming restaurant located in Madeira, known for its rustic ambiance and homemade food. The establishment offers a variety of traditional entrees and desserts, with the unique concept of placing them all on the table for customers to choose from. The menu features dishes prepared in a wood-fired oven, showcasing both Madeiran and mainland cuisine. Visitors can expect generous portions of delicious food, such as the recommended meat of the day and rump steak.
name: Restaurante Cantinho da Serra
address: Estrada do Pico das Pedras 57, 9230-107 Santana, Portugal

detail_description: Lounge Bar Clube Naval do Seixal is a charming spot located near the harbor in Seixal. The owner, Bruno Castro, is known for his friendly and multilingual nature. This place is popular among swimmers looking for a quick bite to eat. It's recommended to order one of their seafood signature dishes, like fried fish with limpet rice and salad, at least three hours in advance.
name: Lounge Bar Clube Naval do Seixal
address: Cais do, 9270-130 Seixal, Portugal

excerpt: Modern choice with outdoor seating & an open kitchen offering sustainable, elevated dishes.
detail_description: Kampo by Chef Julio Pereira is a modern restaurant with outdoor seating and an open kitchen, offering sustainable and elevated dishes. Located in Funchal, Portugal, the restaurant provides a unique dining experience with a focus on seafood and meatier options. Chef Julio Pereira's creative menu includes fish charcuterie boards, braised tuna with razor clam rice, grouper carpaccio with nori, as well as other innovative dishes.
name: Kampo by Chef Julio Pereira
address: R. da Alfândega 74, São Martinho, 9000-059 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Chalet Vicente is a charming destination that perfectly captures the essence of Madeira's culinary heritage. Nestled in a beautifully renovated space, this restaurant offers an inviting rustic atmosphere complemented by its classic Portuguese dishes. Guests can indulge in local favorites like limpets bathed in garlic butter and succulent beef loin espetada, all while enjoying an impressive selection of Portuguese wines. The cozy garden setting adorned with vibrant plants adds to the overall experience, making it ideal for both casual dining and special gatherings.
name: Chalet Vicente
address: Estrada Monumental, n.º 238,, 9000-100 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in the charming municipality of Câmara de Lobos, Restaurante O Polar is a must-visit for anyone craving authentic Portuguese cuisine. This delightful eatery keeps things refreshingly simple with just two main offerings: perfectly grilled frango (chicken) and espetada (beef skewers). The generous portions are ideal for sharing, making it a great spot for friends or couples.
name: Restaurante O Polar
address: Rua do Pico da Torre 26, 9300-004 Câmara de Lobos, Portugal

name: Viola restaurant
address: nº, Estr. João Gonçalves Zarco 596, 9325-033 Câmara de Lobos, Portugal

name: A Venda do André
address: Estr. João Gonçalves Zarco, Quinta Grande, Portugal

name: Cafetaria Sete Mares
address: Av. Sá Carneiro 3, São Martinho, Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: UauCacau is not your typical restaurant, but it's a must-visit chocolate shop in Funchal. Founded by master chocolatier Tony Fernandes, this place offers an array of delectable chocolate truffles, cakes, and other sweet treats. With over 40 different flavors inspired by the island's products like banana, mango, passion fruit, and Madeira wine, UauCacau promises a unique culinary experience.
name: UauCacau
address: R. Q.Baixo 11, São Martinho, 9000-068 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Restaurante Terreiro Concept, part of the Savoy Group, offers a unique dining experience in Funchal. The establishment is described as a gastro-bar with classy food and service. Set in a charming garden within the Savoy complex, the restaurant provides an upscale dining atmosphere. While prices are on the higher side, patrons praise the good quality of dishes such as pork belly and steak. The outdoor terrace offers a delightful setting for enjoying meals, even without prior reservations.
name: Restaurante Terreiro Concept
address: R. Imperatriz Dona Amelia 107, São Martinho, 9004-542 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Prima Caju is a restaurant in Funchal that offers a menu filled with nutritious options without compromising on taste. The establishment is known for its contemporary atmosphere, complete with hanging plants from the ceiling. It's located in the Caju Le Petit Hotel and offers a variety of dishes such as acai bowls, oatmeal pancakes, eggs served with toast and salad, savory bowls, salads, wraps, and smoothies.
name: Prima Caju
address: Rua da Carreira 108, São Martinho, 9000-042 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The restaurant Casa de Pasto Justiniano is a must-stop when visiting Madeira as the espetadas are outstanding and the interior of the restaurant is quite chilly so make sure to bring a jacket.
name: Casa de Pasto Justiniano
address: Estr. Regional 221 Nº 1, 9270-134 Seixal, Portugal

detail_description: Casa De Palha is a charming family restaurant located in Santana, in the north of Madeira. The restaurant is housed in a rustic cottage with traditional thatched roofs, adding to its cozy and welcoming atmosphere. It offers lesser-known dishes from Madeiran gastronomy, such as carne da noite, providing visitors with an authentic culinary experience. In addition to its indoor dining area, Casa De Palha also features an outdoor space for guests to enjoy their meals.
name: Casa De Palha
address: R. Padre Francisco Marques de Mendoça 5, 9230-143 São Jorge, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled at the lower level of Quinta da Casa Branca, The Dining Room restaurant is housed in an elegant Manor House with a classic dining room and an al fresco terrace. It offers a contemporary and inventive cuisine, providing a caring à la carte menu in a refined environment. The restaurant has been recognized for its selection of products, creativity and presentation, mastery of flavor and cooking techniques, value for money, and consistency. This year's assessments have been more flexible due to the disruptions.
name: The Dining Room restaurant at Quinta da Casa Branca
address: R. da Casa Branca 7, São Martinho, 9000-088 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: Nestled in the charming Rua de Santa Maria, Restaurante Gavião Novo is a delightful gem that showcases the best of local cuisine. This cozy eatery is beloved by both locals and visitors alike, offering an inviting atmosphere where you can savor expertly grilled limpets and fresh parrotfish. The menu also features succulent flambeed steaks drizzled with Roquefort sauce, making it a must-visit for meat lovers.
name: Restaurante Gavião Novo
address: Rua de Santa Maria 131, 9060-291 Funchal, Portugal

name: Dona Amelia Restaurant
address: R. Imperatriz Dona Amelia 83, São Martinho, 9000-018 Funchal, Portugal

detail_description: The Ritz Madeira is a historic restaurant located on Avenida Arriaga in Funchal. It offers a blend of classic charm and contemporary cuisine, making it one of the city's oldest dining establishments. The restaurant provides both indoor and outdoor seating, allowing patrons to savor their meals while taking in the lively atmosphere of the city square. The menu showcases a diverse selection of European and Madeiran dishes, featuring fresh seafood, succulent steaks, and vegetarian choices.
name: The Ritz Madeira
address: Av. Arriaga 33, São Martinho, 9000-060 Funchal, Portugal

name: The Town
address: R. Portão de São Tiago 19C, 9060-250 Funchal, Portugal
